### Approaches to styling
1.External
2.Internal
3.Inline

1) External styling
->Considered best practice for most web development projects. Allows developers to change the styling of an entire website from a single style sheet.
Examples:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">


2) Internal styling
->Embedded between the <head> tags of an HTML document.
Styles all elements within a single document. Uses the <style> tag.
Examples:
<style>
h1 { color: blue; }
</style>


2) Inline styling
->Embeds styling withing HTML elements, usually in the same instance in which elements are created.
Examples:

<h1 style="color:red;">Hello</h1>



### commenting in CSS
-> Developers usually insert comments to specify the purpose of the style sheet or to include author details.

->To comment in CSS, we use the following notation:
    /*comment*/

